content.text:
And it will be that when they say to you, ‘Where should we go?’ then you are to tell them, ‘Thus says Yahweh:
“Those destined for death, to death;
And those destined for the sword, to the sword;
And those destined for famine, to famine;
And those destined for captivity, to captivity.”’

And I will winnow them with a winnowing fork
At the gates of the land;
I will bereave them of children; I will make My people perish;
They did not repent of their ways.

Their widows will be more numerous before Me
Than the sand of the seas;
I will bring against them, against the mother of a choice man,
A destroyer at noonday;
I will suddenly bring down on her
Anguish and terror.

She who bore seven sons languishes;
Her breathing is labored.
Her sun has set while it was yet day;
She has been shamed and humiliated.
So I will give over their survivors to the sword
Before their enemies,” declares Yahweh.

Yahweh said, “Surely I will set you free for purposes of good;
Surely I will cause the enemy to intercede with you
In a time of disaster and a time of distress.
